No need to uninstall FL Studio 10!  Disconnect from your internet first! Right click the install file downloaded here, run it as administrator.  When you get to the screen that asks you if you want to install it for ALL users or the current user only, go back to the files that you just downloaded and go into the Reg Key folder.  Double-click the FLRegKey file and accept registry changes.  Then go back to the installer and click next.

When the install finishes, un-check the "run FL Studio 11" button.  Just to be safe, I double-clicked the FLRegKey file again to re-apply changes to the registry.  Then I opened FL Studio 11 and it is WORKING LIKE A CHARM!!!!!!!
